The Vice President spoke with Turkish Prime Minister Erdogan about the security situation in Mosul, Iraq, where ISIL has taken control of parts of the city and seized the Turkish consulate, as well as Turkish personnel as hostages. The Vice President condemned ISIL's actions, called for the safe return of the Turkish personnel, and expressed support for Iraqi and Kurdish security forces in combating the ISIL threat. The United States is ready to assist Turkey in bringing back its citizens and will stay in contact with the Turkish and Iraqi governments to resolve the security situation.